@fn  void ecc_compute_bytes(const uint8_t *sector, const uint16_t *row, int rowlen, uint8_t &val1, uint8_t &val2)

@brief   -------------------------------------------------
           ecc_compute_bytes - calculate an ECC value (P or Q)
         -------------------------------------------------.

@param   [in]     data         The sector data array.
@param   [in]     sectorOffset Offset into the sector data.
@param   [in]     row          The row.
@param   [in]     rowlen       The rowlen.
@param   [in,out] val1Index    Index of the first value.
@param   [in,out] val2Index    Index of the second value.

 @fn  void ecc_generate(uint8_t *sector)

 @brief   -------------------------------------------------
            ecc_generate - generate the P and Q ECC codes for a sector, overwriting any
            existing codes
          -------------------------------------------------.

 @param [in,out]  sector  If non-null, the sector.
Generates P and Q ECC codes for a CD-ROM sector, overwriting any existing ECC data in place.
The byte array containing the sector data (must be at least 2352 bytes per sector).
The zero-based offset within  where the sector begins.

member.returns:
HufferrNone on success;
HufferrInvalidData if the data is malformed;
HufferrInputBufferTooSmall on overflow.

HufferrNone on success;
HufferrInvalidData if the data is malformed;
HufferrInputBufferTooSmall on overflow.
